cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.HC

The paper proposes a fully-automated framework for RBD detection using machine learning techniques. The study involves the analysis of polysomnography data, which is a common application of machine learning in healthcare. The use of Random Forest classifiers and feature extraction from EEG, EOG, and EMG channels suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the incorporation of sleep architecture and sleep stage transitions suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of machine learning for medical diagnosis also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
